## ⚙️ Local Setup

### 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/YOUR_REPO_NAME.git
cd YOUR_REPO_NAME
```

---

## 🖥️ Backend Setup

```bash
cd server
npm install
cp .env.example .env
npm run dev
```

Add your backend environment variables in `server/.env`:

```env
MONGO_URL=your_mongodb_connection_string
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key

AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your_aws_access_key
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your_aws_secret_key
AWS_REGION=your_aws_region
AWS_BUCKET_NAME=your_s3_bucket_name

CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:5173
PORT=5000
```

Backend will run on:

```bash
http://localhost:5000
```

---

## 🌐 Frontend Setup

```bash
cd client
npm install
cp .env.example .env
npm run dev
```

Add your frontend environment variable in `client/.env`:

```env
VITE_API_URL=/api
```

Frontend will run on:

```bash
http://localhost:5173
```

---

## 🚀 Production Deployment

<table>
  <tr>
    <td width="50%">
      <h3>Backend — Render</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Deploy the <code>server/</code> folder</li>
        <li>Add env variables from <code>server/.env.example</code></li>
        <li>Set <code>CLIENT_URL</code> to your Vercel frontend URL</li>
      </ul>
    </td>
    <td width="50%">
      <h3>Frontend — Vercel</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Deploy the <code>client/</code> folder</li>
        <li>Add <code>VITE_API_URL</code></li>
        <li>Redeploy after adding env variables</li>
      </ul>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>

### Backend Environment

```env
MONGO_URL=
JWT_SECRET=
GROQ_API_KEY=
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
AWS_REGION=
AWS_BUCKET_NAME=
CLIENT_URL=https://ai-resume-analysis-wheat.vercel.app
PORT=5000
```

### Frontend Environment

```env
VITE_API_URL=https://YOUR-SERVICE.onrender.com/api
```

---

## 🔐 CORS Setup

Make sure your backend allows your deployed frontend URL.

Correct:

```bash
https://ai-resume-analysis-wheat.vercel.app
```

Wrong:

```bash
https://ai-resume-analysis-wheat.vercel.app/
```

Avoid adding a trailing slash in `CLIENT_URL`.

